South Korea’s Bahk Says Global Double-Dip Slowdown Unlikely

-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 
2011-06-15T04:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/south-korea-s-bahk-says-global-double-dip-slowdown-unlikely.html
The global economy is unlikely to
slip into a “double-dip” slowdown even as emerging countries may
see high inflation and slower economic growth,  South Korea ’s
finance minister Bahk Jae Wan said.  Bahk also said in a speech to be delivered to a local forum
in  Seoul  today that the government will focus on job creation
and price stability to help keep the economy on a growth path.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Eunkyung Seo in Seoul at 
